title.rendered: Delhi vs Gujarat, Indian T20 League 2023: Today’s Fantasy Team, Probable Playing XIs, Pitch Report & Fantasy Tips

content.rendered:
Delhi vs Gujarat Fantasy Team

We have opted for a fantasy cricket team on basis of probable XIs, recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Probable Delhi & Gujarat Playing XIs

Delhi: David Warner* (c), Prithvi Shaw, Mitchell Marsh*, Sarfaraz Khan (wk), Rilee Rossouw*, Rovman Powell*, Axar Patel, Kuldeep Yadav, Chetan Sakariya, Khaleel Ahmed, Mukesh Kumar

Gujarat: Wriddhiman Saha (wk), Shubman Gill, Sai Sudharshan, Hardik Pandya (c), David Miller*, Rahul Tewatia, Rashid Khan*, Mohammed Shami, Alzarri Joseph*, Joshua Little/Odean Smith*, Yash Dayal

Arun Jaitley Stadium, Delhi Pitch Report for Delhi vs Gujarat Match

Venue: Arun Jaitley Stadium, Delhi

(Based on the last three competitive T20s)      

1st innings average score: 179

2nd innings average score: 186

Wickets per innings: 6

Type: Good for batting

Wins

Batting 1st: 33%

Batting 2nd: 67%

Fantasy Tips of The Day

Before 2022, Alzarri Joseph took 36 wickets in as many games. However, his wicket-taking ability since then has significantly improved: 58 wickets in 42 games.

In the same duration, Axar Patel’s batting average shot up from 19 to 30. He also has venue numbers in his favour, scoring 195 runs at 39.

Wriddhiman Saha (129 runs and four catches) and Rashid Khan (six wickets and four catches) featured in the Best11 for five consecutive T20s.

In the only game Gujarat played against Delhi last season, Shubman Gill hammered 84 off 46 including bonus points for 12 boundaries. In his last 10 games, he hit two hundreds, a fifty, and two thirties.

David Warner’s numbers at the venue make a good reading. For an opener to average 31 in as many games is an impressive feat.

Chetana Sakariya’s death bowling – thanks to his variations – scales up his chances of taking more wickets. In his last five outings, he grabbed 12 wickets.

In his last 20 T20s, Rilee Rossouw registered only one single-digit score, overall hammering 697 runs at 37.

Mohammad Shami has taken a mere seven wickets in 15 T20s at the venue.

In the last three games at the venue, spinners accounted for 45% of the wickets.

Ready with your team? Download the My11Circle fantasy app and get started!
